	"system": {
		"description": "<p>Calendula has a self-supporting growth form and broad leaves. Flowers are usually orange or yellow in color, and are multipellated. It thrives in well-drained, sunny soil, and can grow to a little over 1 foot tall. The petals have anti-inflammatory and purifying properties, and are effective in treating virulent wounds and promoting tissue regeneration.</p>\n<p><em><strong>Effect.</strong></em> When applied to a creature below its hit point maximum but unable to benefit from magical healing, a poultice made from the crushed petals provides 1d8 hit points of healing.</p>",
